To read more about our classroom library, click the link in my profile! 📚

node.text:
I started using a word wall a couple years ago and it’s made a HUGE impact.

When students interact with it and refer to it, they’re able to really integrate and apply these words.

We display our Greek and Latin roots, our academic vocabulary cards, and our spelling words.

Do you use anything similar?

node.text:
When students enter each day, they move their magnet on the little board. It helps me put in the correct lunch count AND it shows any absences.

These magnets (from Daiso; I added the vinyl) have lasted almost seven years! Practically a miracle! 😉

The agenda labels are a freebie on my website. Link in profile!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jill ❤️ Hello Fifth in California.

node.text:
This is such a quick and easy way to see who isn’t in class.

The cones are from the Target dollar spot and I added vinyl.

Whether they’re headed to the office or the restroom or they’re out for the whole day, the cone gets popped on their spot. This way, we can make sure to pick up their work or leave necessary materials.

I have six or seven of these and they just sit by the door, making it easy to grab if needed!

node.text:
The grammar boot camp is HERE!

This resource is a GREAT way to assess what your students already know or remember. Then, they’ll engage in hands-on activities to help them practice and play with parts of speech.

The boot camp covers common nouns, proper nouns, adjectives, verbs, adverbs, conjunctions, pronouns and prepositions.

Link in profile to check it out!

node.text:
Our rooms have these built in cubbies (🎉) but they always looked cluttered. So a few years ago, I bought dishpans from Target and slid them in.

They fit perfectly and conceal all sorts of books and headphones and folders.

I sat down this week and wrote about some other organizational systems that we use and love.

Click the link in my profile to check it out! ❤️

The presidential study resource is ready for YOU!

This is something I’ve wanted to do for awhile and I know you’ll love it. This can be used during morning meetings or even as a thinking warm up in social studies, writing, or reading.

It includes anchor charts, student report options, timeline pieces, and more.

It’s on sale for the first 24 hours. Link in profile! ❤️

Command Strips keep it perfectly adhered to the board but there are also holes in case you want to drill it somewhere.

Link in profile for one I love! 📝

Our state studies board is up and ready to go!

We will track what we cover on this map I got from the Target dollar spot about five years ago. Student-created maps that go above and beyond will get displayed.

Link in profile for the resources we use all year.

node.text:
When we celebrate a birthday, kids get to select a circus animal (Target dollar spot) to sit on their desk for the day.

I know it sounds bizarre but they love it. Promise. 😂

I had this bowl so I added some vinyl and popped the animals in!

Cute pencil lamp from Ikea. ✏️
